params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. The relative name of the root asset. Can only be an organization number (such as "organizations/123"), or a project id (such as "projects/my-project-id") or a project number (such as "projects/12345").

params.name: data.read_time
params.description: Timestamp to take an asset snapshot. This can only be set to a timestamp in the past or of the current time. If not specified, the current time will be used. Due to delays in resource data collection and indexing, there is a volatile window during which running the same query may get different results.

params.name: data.asset_types
params.description: A list of asset types of which to take a snapshot for. Example: "google.compute.disk". If specified, only matching assets will be returned.

params.name: data.content_type
params.description: Asset content type. If not specified, no content but the asset name will be returned.

params.name: data.output_config
params.description: Required. Output configuration indicating where the results will be output to. All results will be in newline delimited JSON format.
